<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="360" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1218,1927]" pageId="4" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1794,1819]" pageId="4" pageNumber="360">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[322,414,1795,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simlis">
<emphasis box="[322,414,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="360">S. simlis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[627,765,1795,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Stenotortor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malayana">
<emphasis box="[627,765,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="360">S. malayana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having a large black spot on the second apical cell of forewing and in having differently curved long processes of the aedeagus—in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Wilson" authorityYear="2018" box="[1106,1179,1830,1854]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[1106,1179,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="360">similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are parallel to the shaft whereas in 
<taxonomicName box="[353,463,1867,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Stenotortor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malayana">
<emphasis box="[353,463,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="360">malayana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are strongly divergent. It also resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[1017,1212,1867,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sandakanensis">
<emphasis box="[1017,1212,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="360">S. sandakanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the structure of aedeagus, but has two pairs of apical processes on the aedeagus compared to one in 
<taxonomicName box="[1092,1255,1902,1926]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sandakanensis">
<emphasis box="[1092,1255,1902,1926]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="360">sandakanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
